# ============================================================
# ROOT SUMMARY
# ============================================================

QuickForecast exists to help a user move quickly from
demand expectation to business opportunity draft.

It must remain useful in short work windows,
while QuickForecast Pro supports governed enterprise-linked operation.

# ============================================================
# LAYER SUMMARY
# ============================================================

010.constitution:
Defines QuickForecast as a field-ready application that connects
forecasts to action, proposal, and profit preview,
while preserving ERP coexistence and explicit authority boundaries.

020.architecture:
Defines the Forecast -> Action -> Proposal -> Profit workbench structure,
with mobile-first and local-first design.

030.model:
Defines forecast, signal, scenario, action, proposal, profit,
approval, sync, share, handoff, history, validation, error,
and UI support models.

040.runtime:
Defines local-first runtime, interruption tolerance,
and QuickForecast Pro-linked governed runtime behavior.

050.flow:
Defines the working sequence from forecast drafting
to proposal, profit preview, sharing, approval, and ERP handoff.

060.integration:
Defines QuickForecast Basic general-signal usage and
QuickForecast Pro enterprise-linked contracts,
including approval, sharing, and ERP handoff boundaries.

070.operations:
Defines operational continuity, failure visibility,
runbook guidance, and QuickForecast Pro recoverability.

080.policy:
Defines tier boundary, explainability, validation threshold,
approval / submission gating, and UI state policy.

090.interface:
Defines the mobile-first screen structure, field specs,
and source-to-output UI continuity.

100.security:
Defines tier boundary security, ERP reference protection,
approval integrity, and submission integrity.

110.infrastructure:
Defines local-first mobile infrastructure
and QuickForecast Pro enterprise-link assumptions.

120.implementation:
Defines implementation priorities for the
Forecast -> Action -> Proposal -> Profit chain.

130.development:
Defines MVP-first development order
and later QuickForecast Pro expansion direction.

900.meta:
Defines review checklists, screen inventory,
code seed note, and traceability support.

# ============================================================
# CONCLUSION
# ============================================================

QuickForecast is not merely a demand forecasting tool.

It is a forecast-originated, proposal-oriented,
high-immediacy business drafting application
for turning business hypotheses into actionable opportunities.


